commit_message:
Add python_provide macro for SUSE

The python_provide macro is used in Fedora packages to automatically
insert Provides: and Obsoletes: for python2/python3 packages. Its
usage is described in detail in [1], in short we need a python2 and
python3 subpackage definition like:

%package -n python2-%{srcname}
Summary:        %{sum}
%{?python_provide:%python_provide python2-%{srcname}}

%description -n python2-%{srcname}
Package description

%package -n python3-%{srcname}
Summary:        %{sum}
%{?python_provide:%python_provide python3-%{srcname}}

%description -n python3-%{srcname}
Package description

And python2-%{srcname} would then have
  Provides: python2-%{srcname}
  Provides: python-%{srcname}
  Obsoletes: python-%{srcname} < %{epoch}:%{version}-%{release}

[1] - https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Packaging:Python#Provides

